html:
December 13, 2024

Share this

Twelve moody holiday art prints that make inexpensive holiday decor.

One of my favorite inexpensive ways to add some festive holiday touches around the house is with printable art. I replace random framed art here and there with pretty Christmas prints. 

It's SO easy to either print these at home, or send off to a quick printing service like CVS or Walgreens. I usually use smaller sizes like 8x10 and below, but you can have larger sized printed and shipped to you in a few days. 

I've shared a ton of FREE Christmas printables that you can download and print at home for next to nothing. 

Today I've rounded up twelve moodier prints for the season that give such a cozy vibe, I love them all! All of these are under $5 (at the time of this post). 

If you saw my Santa-themed foyer last week, you saw the beautiful Santa art I used there: 

This post may contain affiliate links for your convenience.

I may earn a small commission when you make a purchase through links. 

I also replaced the art in a couple of frames on my office bookshelves: 

The reflection from the glass was making them hard to see, so I just moved the glass to the back of the frame: 

That Christmas library art is a portrait orientation, so I just cropped it to fit my landscape frame. 

I've shared a ton of FREE Christmas printables that you can download and print at home for next to nothing. Years ago I downloaded a bunch of these fun ornament patent prints from that list: 

I used to just tack them up onto my office frames with tape, but this year I've placed them all over in or on frames: 

I always use a couple of these cheap art prints on our kitchen shelves as well:

Isn't that Christmas mixer art so cute! I just love it! (I included a link to that below.)

These can also be printed on matte paper (which gives it a little higher end look), but usually those have to be shipped. 

You can also find many of these prints on canvas! I bought this set of three Christmas canvases and hung them on our staircase wall: 

It's hard to beat that price for three of them!

I gathered twelve moodier holiday prints to share with you today. They are SO lovely...I wish I could use them all in our home!: 

Here are the links for each of these (plus a few pretty options at the end that aren't pictured):

After you pay, you'll get an email from the seller explaining how to download the prints to your phone or desktop computer. Then you can print them however you like. 

I love that all of these are under $5! Holiday art is one of the easiest ways to add to your Christmas decor.
